# Connector benchmarks

New code under `src/nlp_shap/connectors/` needs two layers:

1. **Correctness** — unit/integration tests in `tests/` (TDD)
2. **Speed** — `@pytest.mark.bench` tests in `tests/benchmarks/`, mirroring the connector path

Benchmarks must cover representative operations (typical init, inference/explain call, hot paths). Tests validate correctness; benchmarks measure latency and catch regressions.

- Use the benchmark harness in `tests/conftest.py`
- Run locally: `make bench` (`pytest -m bench --benchmark`)
- Set explicit timing expectations or document baseline in the test when asserting bounds
- Not run in CI — local only
